This paper discusses the benefits of describing the world as information, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the evolution of life and cognition, which can be studied using machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper touches on the concept of complexity, which is a topic in both neural networks and evolutionary algorithms (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the idea of information becoming more complex, which is a topic in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
